allEmails.subject: Conveyor Belt System Tutorial: Step 1
allEmails.message1:
Hey sams yota! 

My name is Ellen DeHudburg and I am a consultant working for the local government. I heard that your airport was interested in expanding its operations and wanted to include the ability to process baggage! Right now it seems as if your passengers have to drag all of their belongings with them onto their flight which I understand that no one likes. I have opened up access for a new guide to you in the eC-Online Learning portal. You're welcome!
allEmails.message2: A new cE-Online Course, Conveyor Belt System, has been enabled in your learning portal. Head over to the Manuals Panel to begin your learning process!
allEmails.signature:
Ellen DeHudburg - Vice President & Senior Consultant at Kopgemanu

Email: ellen.dehudburgkopgemanu
Cell Phone: 00437715693
Visiting Address: Please contact me before visiting

allEmails.subject: Re: Welcome to your airport!
allEmails.message1:
Thank you for our last meeting and I hope you like your new digs. I know it isn't much but hopefully you'll do better than the last person who tried to build our town's proud airport. You've got A LOT of work ahead of you so you'd better get to it. I can't give you any tips because I really don't know how to run an airport but let me remind you that you have a budget to keep to and we count on you to get this place making a profit. Good luck and we'll talk soon I hope, or, well, my people will send you a message.

Here's the most important thing you need to know: 

1. Press TAB to open and close the Management Panel. Here you will find everything about the management perspective such as economy, staffing, purchasing new products, operations and more. This is your control panel! 
2. Use the Manuals Panel for a guided instruction on how to build an airport. It can be pretty difficult so this might be of great assistance. 
3. Press F1 for tips on how to interact with the UI and move about the screen. 

That's all! Best of luck to you!
